  "bib_entries": {
    "51533676": {
      "title": "Anisotropic features of the two-dimensional hydrogen atom in a magnetic field",
      "abstract": "The aim of the current work is the numerical research of the anisotropic characteristics of the two-dimensional hydrogen atom induced by a magnetic field. The ground state energy (GSE) of the two-dimensional hydrogen atom and the corresponding wave function have been numerically calculated in the Born-Oppenheimer approximation and with taking into account the finite mass of the proton. The non-linear dependence of GSE on the angle {\\alpha} between the magnetic field vector and the normal to the plane of electron motion in a wide range of magnetic field strength has been found. The effect of a significant reduction of GSE (up to 1.9-fold) is observed with increasing the angle {\\alpha} up to 90 degrees."
    }
  }
